This was my very first time dining in at this restaurant, and the experience was horrible. I walked in and was shocked there was a very large party sitting in the back way more than 10 people. They were talking so loud and screaming we asked the waiter if we could move the corner table by the window. The food came and as me and my fiancé were trying to talk over the loud noise and music blasting. One of the girls walk over and ask if her friends could take a pic next to the area we were which wasn’t very big. I thought to myself “  ummmm we are in a pandemic” but i said no problem since I didn’t want to ruin their time. After 20 mins of picture taking one girls started moving backwards to try and take a good pic of her friend and nearly backed into our table. Mind you we were the only table eating and took up 5 percent of the space on the restaurant. I expected a manager or someone who worked at the restaurant to walk over and apologize for the inconsideration of the ladies but instead the bartender started blasting meek mill and I’m assuming these girls were in a sorority because they started dancing in formation making a screeching noise. I couldn’t even enjoy the rest of my meal and it looked like no one who worked at the restaurant cared. When the waiter brought the bill, I explained how inconsiderate this was and he responded he knows, he said the party was for 10 and way more people came. We were so annoyed and left. Definitely will not be returning. I can’t even remember how the food tasted with all the extra stuff that was going on.

I'll start by saying I went to this place Nov 2019 but since I have time I decided to write reviews again! This is a small restaurant that has a retro homey/cozy feel to it. We started off with mimosas and coffee and they were all great. Since it was small we definitely got attention from our waiter who kept the drinks coming! We ordered their biscuits which did not disappoint and I was a little sad I didn't get my own side of them. I had their french toast and bacon for brunch which was good. The bacon was a bit overcooked but maybe it was an off day? The removal of the star really comes from the vents blowing out what seemed like chunks of dead skin or just little flakes? Thankfully this happened towards the end of our meal. I'd still recommend this place! We brought up the vent issue and they were quick to turn them off to avoid it from continuously happening.

This is Harlem’s hidden gem right now before it becomes the GO to spot in the near future.  We celebrated my fiancé’s birthday by having a birthday brunch with 12 people.  Setting this brunch was such a delightful process by emailing Nikoa and Brian about the number of people, requesting a prix fix menu, and letting them know the event we were celebrating.  The overall ambiance and decor of the place were very inviting, vintage, spacious, and clean.  The clientele there had a very nice energy and positive vibe.  The food was terrific! Based on the people that attended, they had the shrimp and grits, eggs benedict, scrambled eggs, and southern breakfast. I had the smoked salmon benedict and it was very tasty.  Next, the drinks were on point! Most bottomless brunches offer the water down orange juice and champagne – NOT Ruby’s. The Rum punch packed a punch, the Mimosa was strong, and the Peach Bellini was a hit! The Service was extremely attentive.  Thank you Nikoa and Brian for such a wonderful experience. Look forward to our next visit.

Ruby’s Vintage in Harlem is an amazing space with a great atmosphere and vibes. The restaurant has an upscale and retro aesthetic however it is a great place to unwind and connect with people. The selections on the brunch menu are diverse and filling. My friends and I enjoyed the bottomless cocktail brunch with Southern Breakfast and Shrimp & Grits as our entrees. Our server and the owner were welcoming and genuinely cared about our experience. We will be back to support this Black Owned Business.

Brian and Nikoa have done it again!!!!!   Ruby's Vintage is a place I can bring clients, friends, and that special someone....all with an intention to delight.  The appetizers are scrumptious, the drinks are amazing...and I don't really drink (hehehe), and the service and ambiance are Afropolitan, sophisticated, warm, welcoming and sexy!!!!
